attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit MSB executable, MIPS, MIPS-I version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, stripped

threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This is a MIPS-based IoT botnet agent, likely a variant of the Condi family. The binary enumerates and kills other processes by inspecting `/proc/%d/cmdline` for names like `netstat`, `wget`, and `busybox`. It contains functionality to perform a DDoS attack by sending crafted SSDP M-SEARCH discovery packets. It also includes a downloader component that sends `GET` requests with a custom User-Agent (`Update v1.0`) and can execute arbitrary commands via `/bin/sh`. The presence of the path `/var/Condi` is a strong indicator of this malware family.
